                <h1>What Does a Pop Filter Remove?</h1>
                <p>A pop filter device is designed to reduce or eliminate plosive sounds—such as "P" and "B"—that can create unwanted noise during recording. It also effectively filters out sibilance, high-frequency hissing from "S" sounds, and helps prevent saliva droplets from reaching the microphone, ensuring cleaner audio quality for recordings.</p>
